# Mercury safety (non-negotiable)

Before any DB or backup change, read `src/mercury/core/safety.py` and `execution_policy.py`.

- Backup sources: `*_prod` and `android_permission_intel` only. Never `*_dev`.
- Never drop, overwrite, or restore into `*_prod`.
- `_restorecheck_*` and unknown-role DBs are not backup sources.
- Dry-run is default. Live writes need `dry_run=false` AND `live_actions_enabled=true`.
- ProdтЖТdev sync (future) requires typing `SYNC DEV` after verified prod backup.
- Live SQL must stay read-only (`SELECT`, `SHOW`, `information_schema`). No DDL/DML.
- Never commit `config/local.toml` or passwords.

When adding features: gate writes through `load_execution_policy()` / `ExecutionPolicy.live_execution_allowed()`.

```python
# тЬЕ Check before mariadb-dump or file writes
policy = load_execution_policy()
if not policy.live_execution_allowed():
    return dry_run_result
```

```python
# тЬЕ Validate backup source before planning
assert_safe_backup_source(database_name)
```
